The project explorer panel allows to browse and manage all projects components, arranged in a folder structure in the navigation tree. It comprises two sections:

- [Flows](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-project-explorer-panel#flows)

- [Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-project-explorer-panel#resources)

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## **Flows**
**Flows **are automatically generated by the system for each end-to-end project workflow defined in the pipeline; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click on a flow to highlight the corresponding workflow; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Viewing and editing the details of a flow
- Move your mouse pointer over the name of a flow; the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon appears.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click![](data:image/png;base64,) to open the **Flow details **panel on the right; for example:![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- View and edit the required flow properties.

**Field**

**Description**

**Flow name**

Name of the flow displayed in the **Flows **section on the left

**Flow description**

Description of the flow

**Flow Items**

Automatically generated list of the pipeline elements included in this flow.

> Tip

Click on the name of an element to highlight it in the pipeline.

## **Resources**
The **Resources **section lists all projects resources, arranged under the corresponding grouping folder in the navigation tree.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The available project resources are:

**Icon**

**Grouping Folder**

**Resource Type**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Readers**

- [DT3 CSV Reader](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-csv-reader) 

- [DT3 Flat File Reader](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-flat-file-reader) 

- [DT3 XML Reader](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-xml-reader)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Mappers**

- [DT3 Mapper](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Writers**

- [DT3 Flat File Writer ](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-flat-file-writer)

- [DT3 XML Writer](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-xml-writer)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Catalogs**

- [DT3 Catalog Component](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-catalog-component)

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**WebServices**

- [DT3 Web Service Component](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-web-service-component)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**DataQualitites**

- [DT3 Data Quality Component](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-data-quality-component)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Unsupported**

This section groups any resources that are currently not supported by the new Data Transformation HTML5 UI, that is, elements that can only be added and managed using the classic editor.

> Note

For more information, refer to the legacy [Data Transformation and Enrichment User Manual](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Data%2BTransformation%2Band%2BEnrichment%2BUser%2BManual), in particular: [Pipeline Editor](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/3%2B-%2BPipeline%2BEditor).

> Note

If a category is empty, i.e. it does not contain any active or inactive resources, it is not displayed in the project explorer tree.

### Actions on project resources
- Move your mouse pointer over the name of a resource and click the ![](data:image/png;base64,)  icon that appears to display the context menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the required action:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

Applies to

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Edit**

Open the resource in the dedicated editor.

> Note

For more information, see: [Configuring DT3 Project Resources.](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources)

- Active resources

- Inactive resource

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Details**

Open the Details panel to view and edit the resource's details.

> Note

For more information, see [Viewing and editing the details of a resource](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-project-explorer-panel#viewing-and-editing-the-details-of-a-resource) below.

> Tip

When the Details panel is open, it is possible to view the details of another resource by clicking on a different elem pipeline editor or resource in the project explorer panel.

> Note

This action is not available for catalogs.

- Active resources

- Inactive resource

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Remove**

Remove the resource from the pipeline.

> Note

The resource will still be available in the project, and can be put back into the pipeline or permanently deleted.

> Note

This action is not available for catalogs.

- Active resources

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Put back**

Put the resource back into the pipeline.

> Important

The original position of the resource in the pipeline and all its previous connections will not be restored.

> Note

This action is not available for catalogs.

- Inactive resource

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently delete the resource from the project.

> Important

This action cannot be undone. Before proceeding, the system will display a warning and request confirmation:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

- Inactive resource

> Inactive resources

Inactive resources are resources that have been removed from the pipeline, but not permanently deleted from the project. They are listed in the project explorer panel in light gray; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Viewing and editing the details of a resource
- Move your mouse pointer over the name of a resource in the project explorer panel (or over a pipeline element) and click the  ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon that appears to display the context menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**Details**). The **Details **panel is displayed on the right; for example:![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- View and edit the required properties.

**Field**

**Description**

**Name**

Name of the resource displayed in the **Resources **section on the left and in the pipeline, if in use

> Important

The name of the resource must be unique in the pipeline.

**Description**

*(optional) *Brief description of the resource

**Type**

*(only available for Reader and Writer resources)*

Select the resource type from the drop-down menu.

**Included in flow**

Automatically generated list of the flows that include this resource. 

> Tip

Click on the name of a flow to highlight it in the pipeline.
